description:
This is a 6 minute workout called 'Hydrow Games: Race Day with Aquil and Laine' from the channel Aquil Abdullah.
The workout falls under Cardio/Indoor rowing.
It's suitable for Advanced fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Competitor and The Adrenaline Rush vibe.
The The Competitor vibe means Gamified, leaderboard-driven, full-send energy. This is especially good for Those who need to chase a score or beat their own record. The The Adrenaline Rush vibe means Heart-racing, full-body intensity, unpredictable challenges. This is especially good for Those who crave challenge, variety, and adrenaline..
The technique difficulty is Intermediate.
The effort required is Challenging.

Original workout description: Feel the competitive spirit with Aquil and Laine in the second race of the Hydrow Games on the Charles River! This 5-minute drive is all about bringing your everything to the race. Start strong at a rhythm of 32, then settle into a powerful 28. Throughout the race, you'll make strategic moves, pushing your limits and focusing on technique. With motivational guidance, Aquil and Laine remind you that wherever you start is where the race begins. You can do anything for some time, just take it one stroke at a time. Embrace the challenge and leave it all on the water. Max rhythm: 32. Format: Intervals...
